parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure due to Radiator Coolant Leak
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. This issue can also lead to costly repairs, which can be a significant financial burden.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle loses power
the transmission fluid is contaminated with coolant
the radiator is leaking coolant
the vehicle is unable to shift gears
the transmission warning light is on.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Radiator Failure causing Transmission Coolant Leak
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radiator can cause the transmission to fail, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The radiator is leaking coolant
the transmission fluid is contaminated with coolant
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle loses power
the transmission warning light is on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radiator can cause coolant to leak into the transmission, leading to transmission failure, loss of power, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience hesitation or loss of power
the transmission may slip or fail to engage
the radiator fluid may mix with transmission fluid
and the vehicle may stall or fail to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure Due to Radiator Coolant Contamination
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause loss of power, stalling, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience hesitation or loss of power
the transmission may slip or fail to engage
the radiator fluid may mix with transmission fluid
and the vehicle may stall or fail to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain tensioning system can cause engine failure, loss of power, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience unusual noises
vibrations
or engine stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel gauge can cause the driver to run out of fuel, leading to accidents or stranding.
symptoms: The fuel gauge displays incorrect readings
sticks to a specific level
or fails to register fuel levels
leading to uncertainty about the amount of fuel remaining.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel sending unit can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to uncertainty about the amount of fuel remaining and potentially causing accidents or stranding.
symptoms: The fuel gauge displays incorrect readings
sticks to a specific level
or fails to register fuel levels
leading to uncertainty about the amount of fuel remaining.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or stranding.
symptoms: The transmission exhibits stuttering or hesitation during acceleration
or fails to respond to acceleration attempts.
